GitHub Action for Password Strength Check

Implementing a GitHub Action to enforce strong password policies within your workflows.
How it Works:

Utilizes regular expressions (regex) to check the strength of passwords entered by users or stored in repositories.
Benefits:

Enhanced Security: Ensures that passwords meet minimum complexity requirements, reducing the risk of unauthorized access or data breaches.
Compliance: Helps maintain compliance with security standards and regulations that mandate strong password policies.
User Education: Promotes awareness of good password hygiene among developers and contributors.
